<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>My concerns in <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">blue</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>italics</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Mercenary 1.65 Team Lead Report -=DRAFT=-<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>OVERVIEW</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Mercenaries are perceived as a fairly complete class that mostly suffers an identity crisis. This is true only because Mercenaries mature with Realm Ranks. The increased desirability of Mercenaries in RvR groups has more to do with access to powerful cheap RA's than because of the class's function. Continuing to have to rely on these cheap, effective (overpowered?) RA's to define our role is an undesired situation. Mercenaries need unique effective tools that allows us to fulfil our role regardless of Realm Rank or balancing actions to RA's.<br>
<br>
The only changes to Mercenaries in 1.65 came in the form of tweaks to the Crush style list. The change to Bludgeon was well received. It is too early to pass judgement on the changes to Concussion &amp; Bone Crusher.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CONCERNS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The Role of the Light Tank. In 1.62, Light Tanks were defined as positional fighters, or assist tanks. In this regard, Mercenaries suffer an identity crisis since very few of our tools are tailored to achieve this. Our Dual Wield spec line appears to be nothing more than another base style list. The few styles that fit our role suffer penalties that make its usefulness questionable, given other options in our base style lists. See Specline Issues below.<br>
<br>
Pure Tank Realm Abilities. It is access to these Realm Abilities (RA's) that is giving Mercenaries a rise in popularity. The Prevent Flight RA combined with our ability to Dual Wield is unmatched in Albion. Our access to Determination, especially above level 3, further compounds the issue by ensuring we're able to be in position to Prevent Flight over the course of an entire battle. If at any time these RA's are decreased in effectiveness, so will the Mercenary's role in RvR.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Very true. Those cheap realm abilities did more to increase the value of the class than any change since release.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SPECLINE ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dual Wield:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- This specline should reflect our new role as positional fighters or assist tanks, yet does not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>From experience we are as much a reactive tank than a positional one. I for one consider our best styles are reactive ones. They however do not have enough bang for the trouble we go through to pull them off. (Both the reactives and the positional styles)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- One of our positionals, Flank, suffers serious penalties due to its lack of To-Hit bonus. In PvE, the only encounters challenging enough for a full group or a larger force, will be very purple. Such high level monsters renders a no To-Hit style like Flank and its followup, ineffective. In RvR this is also seen when fighting Keep Lords. Against other players, the fluidity of a battle prevents the constant re-use of a side positional. With Flank's lack of consistancy, it is more efficient to rely on some other style to hit for less damage, more often.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I agree that the no to hit bonus doesen't help but here is anoter problem with flank. It's mostly used against casters in RvR as they are the only classes that doesen't move around much so it gives us a chance to pull it off. The first hit is almost always Bladeturned after that they usually turn their backs to us as they run away making flank a very situational style that never gets any real use. Eighter make it a very worthwhile style to use or give it something special. Reavers have a side positional chain that does loads of damage since it lifetaps as well. I think something like a short stun (3sec like blademasters) or some other effect should be used to make it a good style.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- The Damage vs. Endurance cost for Misty Gloom arguably makes this the worst style in this spec line.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To fit mythic views this style should only be reduced in end cost (heavy reduction needed) the damage should stay the same. Right now Inflame is much better than Misty Gloom in all aspects</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- Dark Tendrils was changed in 1.62 to be a Parry reactional. Given the popularity of the Reflection-&gt;Hypnotic Darkness chain for the Stun effect and Dual Shadows for the Bleed Effect, Dark Tendrils is rarely used.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I think the Dark tendrills change was good but the bleed damage should be increased to at least the same level as Dual shadows since it's a reactive style.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Shadow's Edge + Eclipse\Penumbra</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>We lack a good Back positional style in DW. So far every merc i know use their base styles back positional since the 2 back chains we have are not better if not worst than the base ones. Those 2 chains also start both with the same style (Shadow's Edge) and their followups are very similar. Penumbra should be increased in damage by a fair margin to make it really a decent followup.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Crush: ???<br>
<br>
