<br>
Shield: <br>
<br>
- Mercenaries who choose a hybrid configuration including shield spec are penalized for doing so. The interface to change from weapon to shield is time consuming and disliked. While a shield is equipped, the Mercenary is penalized by having unused points invested in the Dual Wield spec as well as being unable to use Dual Wield styles. Mercenaries have very little reason to wear shields since the defensive playstyle is better suited to other classes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I think the ability to Hotkey a shield in our 2h Slot is still something we would like very much. Even if most of us do not spec very high in shield we still would like to have access to it without constantly switching stuff in our backpacks.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Parry:<br>
<br>
- Parry is the main means of defense for a Mercenary and is the only specline that does not add increased utility the further you buy into it. That claim true?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Parry is a completly passive defence like evade is but unlike evade it is not a free ability. We must invest quite a load of points in this ability to benefit from it. The benefits are marginal at best granting a whooping .5% per spec point. <br>
Parry should get styles + abilities in a reactive form to compete with shield that gets defensive abilities.<br>
<br>
For example instead of Guard we should get Counterattack : Gives 1 free attack (1hit unstyled)on the mob that hit the person you were watching with counterattack.<br>
We could also have our own form of Engage with parry: Same as engage but gives a chance to counterattack everytime you parry. Could be more than 1 lvl of it atained at different specs to increase the chances to counterattack.<br>
<br>
Anything to make parry a worthwhile ability to have.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CLASS ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Charge:<br>
<br>
- Since the introduction of the Charge ability to Light Tanks, better forms of Endurance Regen. as well as Endurance Potions have been introduced to the game. This ability is now nearly redundant since groups with a source of End. Regen nearly always travel with sprint active, which is the equivalent of an unlimited Charge ability. For the Mercenary in a group without End. Regen., the ability is still rendered useless if the opponent has End. Regen. OR if the opponent uses an End. Potion. The opponent can continue sprinting long after the 10 seconds from Charge have elapsed and not worry about Mercenaries catching up since Charge offers no speed increase.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To make charge worthwhile it should be Slightly faster than Sprint (aka Speed 3) but still cost end (Maybe more end than sprint) It would still last 10 seconds and be on a 5 minute timer making it something we could use but not overpower us. <br>
They should remove the enemy target requirement of this ability nothing makes you loose more time than having to select an enemy while trying to catch up with it.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
Dirty Tricks:<br>
<br>
- This ability is highly situational as well as completely ineffective against 17 of 39 classes in the game.<br>
If the Mercenary community wants me to bring up the issue of DT and resists, I'll want some logs that lend weight to my request.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How about making it Nearsight the caster for the same duration as it makes opponents fumble? I think dirt in the eyes prety much blinds anyone. No?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Flury</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>This ability should be useable in PvE as well. I see no reason a low damage insta DD on a 2 minute timer would overpower us in PvE. It would also make Gaheris mercs somewhat more useful since they have no way of using this ability there.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
OTHER ISSUES<br>
<br>
- Void needs to be replaced by a worthwhile RA<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Something that could enable us to attack more than 1 opponent at once in close combat would help us much more than a once every 10 minute crap style.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
- Mercenaries question why we do not gain access to the Avoid Pain RA.<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Legitimate question since Berzerkers gets it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- First Aid from it's description is considered a downtime helper instead of a combat useable ability. While i have no quarel with this application, i often wonder why it's on a 15 minute timer while other similar abilities like MCL are on a 5 minute timer. Reducing it to a 5 minute timer like other abilities would help it live up to it's description instead of just being a useless requirement for Ignore Pain</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
- It has been confirmed that Evade I does not scale equally compared to higher levels of Evade when enhanced by buffs.<br>
I need to get the logs and results of the tests already done, as well as supplement what testing is done to show a trend across all levels of Evade.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I saw some tests made that proved this point. It would really help if we knew the exact formula how evade works.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
ITEM PROBLEMS<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Caer sidi set of armor still has parts that have a cold 95dd reactive on them. I really think something as hard to acquire as a sidi set of armor should at least have something unique on it. Legs and Arms have a 150 abaltive that is unique.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
DOCUMENTATION ISSUES<br>
<br>
- When I activate Dirty Tricks, I get the message &quot;You flings a cloud of dirt in your eyes! &quot; it should read something else. For example, &quot;You grab a handful of dirt!&quot; <br>
- When Dirty Tricks procs, there is no message. It should a provide a &quot;You throw dirt at XXX's eyes!&quot;. <br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.<br>
