I'm not getting this from Kerrec's report. And I don't see a reason that you should flame him simply because he disagreed with you.<br>
<br>
I'm only a level 45 Merc at the moment, and my experience is generally PvE only, so I can't really comment on much of the report, as it deals almost exclusively with RvR issues. Of the few PvE issues:<br>
<br>
While it would be wonderful to have Flurry work in PvE, and I don't think it would be terribly unbalancing, it might have lower level solo PvE effects. At level 35, Flurry was hitting for ~200 in the BG, which could overpower soloing of yellow-orange con mobs at that level.<br>
<br>
To-Hit on the Flank Chain could use a boost in PvE as well. Landing Flank isn't generally difficult, but the follow up lands perhaps 33-50% of the time on red+ cons, although does nice damage when it does land. <br>
<br>
Generally speaking, the DW styles are good for PvE. I'm looking forward to the style review though because I'm hoping that Mythic will add more effects than just the general Bleed/Snare/Atk.Debuff sort of things and make the advanced spec lines more like those given to Reavers, Savages, and VWs. Something like a Dirt effect built into a DW style would be kinda cool.<br>
<br>
There's my input from the lower lvl side of things.<br>
