<br>
No, it's recognizing the reality of the situation.  Mackey, the TL coordinator and the person these TL reports get submitted to, has flat out stated that Determination is overpowered and needs to be nerfed.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, to me Kerrec's report comes across more as &quot;I know you believe that some of our RAs are overpowering, and that is possibly true, but it is those RAs that allow us to be effective at all in the general RvR environment of today, so please keep in mind that simply nerfing those RAs without making other signifigant changes may effectively nerf the class.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is similar to what the Wizard TL had to deal with for 1.65.  There was no question that a VP nerf was incoming.  Rather than not commenting on the issue, in his 1.64 report he offered one way that VP might be changed to meet some of the concerns about it.<br>
<br>
Now, if you did nothing but read the Wizard TL report on its own, it might indeed look like the TL was calling for a VP nerf, but if you understood the context behind it, it made a lot more sense. <p>Acus TwinHammer<br>
